SIMPLE: emboss
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emboss
<hw>Em*boss"</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Embossed</conjf> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Embossing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>em-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + <ets>boss</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>embosser</ets> to swell in bunches.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
raise the surface of into bosses or protuberances; particularly, to
ornament with raised work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Botches and blains must all his flesh <qex>emboss</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To raise in relief from a surface, as an ornament, a
head on a coin, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then o'er the lofty gate his art <qex>embossed</qex>⟦br⟧
Androgeo's death.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Exhibiting flowers in their natural color <qex>embossed</qex> upon
a purple ground.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Emboss
<hw>Em*boss"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Etymology uncertain.]</ety>
<def>To make to foam at the mouth, like a hunted animal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Emboss
<hw>Em*boss"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Pr. & Sp.
<ets>emboscar</ets>, It. <ets>imboscare</ets>, F. <ets>embusquer</ets>,
and E. <ets>imbosk</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hide or conceal in
a thicket; to imbosk; to inclose, shelter, or shroud in a wood.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the Arabian woods <qex>embossed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To surround; to ensheath; to immerse; to
beset.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A knight her met in mighty arms <qex>embossed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboss</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Emboss
<hw>Em*boss"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To seek the bushy forest; to
hide in the woods.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>S.
Butler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embossed</ent>⟦br⟧
